To reproduce this figure you need to download the raw counts data (raw_counts_kallisto.tab) and preprocess it according to Figure1. You also need the âGABA highâ & âGABA lowâ labels for each patient available in GABA labels, the Supplementary Table S12 from the article, along with the rds file Databases_signatures.

Immuno histochemistry (IHC) data is needed to reproduce panel b from this Figure but is only available from the corresponding author upon reasonable request.

Code 
#Needed objects from Figure 1:
#DESEq_Bionikk_vst

###Read data...

DESEq_Bionikk_vst<-readRDS("DESEq_Bionikk_vst.rds")

##Import GABA_labels
GABA_labels<-read.delim("GABA_labels.tab")
GABA_labels$ID<-GABA_labels$Anonym_ID
Clinical_dat_AB_TLSpos<-GABA_labels
##Subset to same samples...
DESEq_Bionikk_vst_AB_TLSpos<-DESEq_Bionikk_vst[,colnames(DESEq_Bionikk_vst)%in%Clinical_dat_AB_TLSpos$ID];dim(DESEq_Bionikk_vst_AB_TLSpos)

##Put in the same order...
DESEq_Bionikk_vst_AB_TLSpos<-DESEq_Bionikk_vst_AB_TLSpos[,order(factor(colnames(DESEq_Bionikk_vst_AB_TLSpos), levels = Clinical_dat_AB_TLSpos$ID))]#reorder names

table(colnames(DESEq_Bionikk_vst_AB_TLSpos)==Clinical_dat_AB_TLSpos$ID)#

#####Analysis on MCP counter
##Calculate other TME related activities using MCP counter...
library(MCPcounter)
library(ggpubr)
library(Hmisc)
library(reshape2)
mcp_scores_updated <- MCPcounter.estimate(DESEq_Bionikk_vst_AB_TLSpos,featuresType = "HUGO_symbols")
mcp_scores_updated<-as.data.frame(t(mcp_scores_updated))

tmp_clinical<-cbind(Clinical_dat_AB_TLSpos,mcp_scores_updated)
filter<-"GABA_Bionikk"

pal_to_use<-c("#E7B800", "#2E9FDF")
 to_plot<-rownames(mcp_scores_updated) 
t<-melt(tmp_clinical[],id.vars=filter, measure.vars=to_plot)
 ##Perform wilcoxon test between  groups, to annotate the boxplots...
comparisons_tmp<-compare_means(formula =as.formula(paste0("value ~",filter)),data = t,method = "wilcox.test",group.by = "variable",p.adjust.method="BH") 
comparisons_tmp<-as.data.frame(comparisons_tmp[order(comparisons_tmp$p),])


###Add median expression values per group and foldchange (to know in which direction it is significant...)
values_tmp<-aggregate(tmp_clinical[, to_plot], list(tmp_clinical[,filter]), mean)
values_tmp2<-t(values_tmp[1,-1])
##For first group
comparisons_tmp[,paste0("mean_",values_tmp[1,1])]<-values_tmp2[comparisons_tmp$variable,]
##For second group
values_tmp3<-t(values_tmp[2,-1])

comparisons_tmp[,paste0("mean_",values_tmp[2,1])]<-values_tmp3[comparisons_tmp$variable,]

print(head(comparisons_tmp))

##Print table...
write.table(comparisons_tmp,file = paste0(file.tmp2,"/MCPcounter_comparisons.tab"),quote = F,sep = "\t")

 
##Order by significance
order_tmp<-as.character(comparisons_tmp$variable[order(comparisons_tmp$p)]) #pvalue
t$variable<-factor(t$variable,levels = order_tmp)

comp<-t

p.list = lapply(levels(t$variable), function(ct){
  
 sub<-comp[comp$variable==ct,]
p = ggplot(sub, aes(y=value,x=filter)) +geom_violin(aes_string(fill = filter), alpha = 0.5,trim = FALSE, position = position_dodge(0.9)) + geom_boxplot(aes_string(color = filter), alpha = 0.5,width=0.1,position = position_dodge(0.9))+
        stat_compare_means(paired = F,method = "wilcox.test",hide.ns = F,label = "p.format",aes(group = GABA_reduced_group)) +
        scale_color_manual(values = c("High_GABA"="#E7B800","Low_GABA"="#2E9FDF")) +scale_fill_manual(values = c("High_GABA"="#E7B80080","Low_GABA"="#2E9FDF80"))+
        ggtitle(ct) + labs(y="GSVA signature", x="Response group")+
        theme_classic() +
        theme(
            plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5),
            axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10),
            axis.title.x = element_text(size = 0),
            axis.title.y = element_text(size = 0),
            legend.position = 'bottom')
p
})

#CombinePlots(p.list,ncol = 6)
ggsave(CombinePlots(p.list,ncol = 6),filename = "Violin_MCPcounter.pdf",width = 20,height = 18)
ggsave(CombinePlots(p.list,ncol = 6),filename = "Violin_MCPcounter.png",width = 20,height = 18)

library(GSVA)

gsva.res_signatures_updated<-GSVA::gsva(expr = as.matrix(DESEq_Bionikk_vst_AB_TLSpos), gset.idx.list = Databases_signatures, method = "gsva", parallel.sz = 15)

All_signatures_updated_tmp2<-as.data.frame(t(gsva.res_signatures_updated))
##Add to clinical
tmp_clinical<-Clinical_dat_AB_TLSpos
print(all(rownames(All_signatures_updated_tmp2)==tmp_clinical$ID))#Must be true
tmp_clinical<-cbind(tmp_clinical,(All_signatures_updated_tmp2))

filter<-"GABA_Bionikk"

##Databases signatures values

Code 
#Needed objects from Figure 1
#counts_kallisto_AB_TLSpos
#Clinical_dat_AB_TLSpos having the GABA_Bionikk column

library(DESeq2)

DESEq_gaba <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = counts_kallisto_AB_TLSpos,
                                        colData = Clinical_dat_AB_TLSpos[,c("ID","GABA_Bionikk")],
                                        design = ~ GABA_Bionikk)

DESEq_gaba

##Run deseq2
DESEq_gaba
dim(DESEq_gaba)

keep <- rowSums(counts(DESEq_gaba)) >= 0
table(keep)
DESEq_gaba <- DESEq_gaba[keep,]

dim(DESEq_gaba)

#check design
design(DESEq_gaba)

#dds_tmp<-estimateSizeFactors(DESEq_taqman, type = 'iterate')

dds_tmp2 <- DESeq(DESEq_gaba)
##Extract results
res_gaba <- results(dds_tmp2, alpha=0.05,contrast=c("GABA_Bionikk", "High_GABA", "Low_GABA"))
#This comparison means that a fold change positive is more expressed in GABA_high; and a foldchange negative is less expressed in R

##Printable
  res_gaba2<-as.data.frame(subset(res_gaba, pvalue < 0.05  )[,c(1:2,5,6)])
res_gaba2$baseMean<-rownames(res_gaba2)
colnames(res_gaba2)<-c("Gene","log2FoldChange","pval","padj")
res_gaba2 <- res_gaba2[order(res_gaba2$pval,decreasing = F),]

write.table(res_gaba,file="Bionikk_GABAhigh_vsLow_FC.tab",row.names = FALSE, quote = FALSE,sep = "\t")


##Volcanoplot
# Create a dataframe from the gene list
df <- data.frame(log2FC = res_gaba$log2FoldChange, pvalue = res_gaba$padj)
rownames(df)<-rownames(res_gaba)

library(EnhancedVolcano)

selected_genes<-c("IGHG1","IGHG2","IGHG3","IGHG4","IGHM","JCHAIN","IGLC1","IGLC2","GZMB","CD163","CD68","ICAM1","CXCL5","FCGR3A","FCGR1A","CCL20","IL6R","IL7R"
                  #
                  )
###Check gaba releted genes
##Load signatures
Manual_signatures<-read_excel("Supplementary_tables.xls", sheet = "Table S12") #Get from the article, Table S12
Manual_signatures<-as.data.frame(Manual_signatures[-1,-1])
Manual_signatures<-as.list(Manual_signatures)
Signatures_GABA<-Manual_signatures[1:4]
#
GABA_genes_all<-unique(unlist())

selected_genes2<-intersect(res_gaba2$Gene[res_gaba2$log2FoldChange>0],GABA_genes_all)
#selected_genes2<-c(selected_genes2,selected_genes2_fgsea)

keyvals.colour <- ifelse(
    abs(df$log2FC) < 0.75 | df$pvalue>=0.05, 'gray',
      ifelse(rownames(df)%in%selected_genes, 'darkblue',
           #  ifelse(rownames(df)%in%selected_genes2, 'darkred',
        ifelse(df$log2FC>=0.75&df$pvalue<0.05, 'firebrick1',"royalblue")))
#)

keyvals.colour[is.na(keyvals.colour)] <- 'gray'
  names(keyvals.colour)[keyvals.colour == 'gray'] <- 'Not sig. or abs(Log2FC)<0.75'
  names(keyvals.colour)[keyvals.colour == 'darkblue'] <- paste0('Immunity related genes (n=',length(selected_genes),")")
  names(keyvals.colour)[keyvals.colour %in% c('firebrick1'
                                             # ,'darkred'
                                              )] <- paste0('Enriched in GABA High (n=',table(keyvals.colour)["firebrick1"]+4,")")
  names(keyvals.colour)[keyvals.colour == 'royalblue'] <- paste0('Enriched in GABA Low (n=',table(keyvals.colour)["royalblue"],")")

p_volcano_gaba<-EnhancedVolcano(df,
                lab = rownames(df),  # Use gene names as labels
                x = 'log2FC',         # Specify log2FC column
                y = 'pvalue',        # Specify p-value column
                #xlim = c(-5, 5),     # Adjust x-axis limits if needed
                title = "Differentially Expressed Genes GABA high vs GABA Low"
                ,pCutoff = 0.05,FCcutoff = 0.75,
                #legendLabels=c('Not sig.','Log2FC','padj','padj & Log2FC'),
                colCustom = keyvals.colour,
                legendPosition = 'right',legendLabSize = 16,legendIconSize = 5.0,
      drawConnectors = TRUE,
    widthConnectors = 0.75,
    selectLab = c(selected_genes,selected_genes2) ##Only label genes of interest...
    ,labFace = 'bold',boxedLabels = TRUE,
    pointSize = c(ifelse(rownames(df)%in%c(selected_genes,selected_genes2), 5, 1))
    ,colAlpha =c(ifelse(rownames(df)%in%c(selected_genes,selected_genes2), 1, 0.1))
    ,xlim = c(-4, 4),ylim = c(0,6)
    )

ggsave(p_volcano_gaba,filename = "VolcanoPlot_GABAhig_vs_Low_Selection.pdf",width = 14,height = 10)
ggsave(p_volcano_gaba,filename = "VolcanoPlot_GABAhig_vs_Low_Selection.png",width = 14,height = 10)
